{
  "texts": [
    "The numerical setup is publicly available on GitHub [1].",
    "The time interval between two subsequent snapshots is set to ∆t = 2.5 • 10 -4 s, corresponding to ∆τ = ∆tU∞/d = 0.0975 convective time units (CTU), and a total number of 500 snapshots in the range 75 ≤ τ ≤ 124 is collected, corresponding to roughly 50 CTU.",
    "The selected time interval only extends over 11 vortex shedding cycles.",
    "This limitation stems from the available memory on a single node of our HPC cluster when computing the SVD of the original CFD data, which is needed for validation.",
    "We define the state vector using the instantaneous velocity fluctuations in all three directions."
  ]
}